(firstQuint)Effect of VSL#3 on Intestinal Permeability in Pediatric Crohn's Disease.

 Children with Crohn's disease have altered intestinal permeability.

 A pilot study in children showed that probiotics may decrease intestinal permeability.

 In this double blind, randomized controlled trial, we will observe the effect of VSL#3 on small bowel permeability using a double sugar absorption test.

 PCDAI was monitored, but not analyzed.

